detaileddescription.para:
T



The type of data stored in the graph vertices. 





graph



The input graph. 




startAirport



The code of the starting airport. 




endAirport



The code of the destination airport. 




A vector of vectors containing the shortest paths.

Example Usage: Graph<string>flightGraph;
//PopulateflightGraph...
stringstartAirport="OPO";
stringendAirport="JFK";
autopaths=findShortestPath(flightGraph,startAirport,endAirport);
//Usepathsforfurtherprocessing...

T



The type of data stored in the graph vertices. 





graph



The input graph. 




distance



A map containing distances from the start airport to each vertex. 




end



The destination airport. 




current



The current airport in the path. 




currentPath



The current path being constructed. 




allPaths



Vector to store all the paths found. 




initialSize



The initial size of the current path vector (default is 2).



Example Usage: Graph<string>flightGraph;
//PopulateflightGraph...
stringstartAirport="OPO";
stringendAirport="JFK";
unordered_map<string,int>distances;//Populatedistancesmap...
vector<vector<string>>paths;
vector<string>currentPath;
backtrackPaths(flightGraph,distances,endAirport,startAirport,currentPath,paths);
//Usepathsforfurtherprocessing...

